<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-558-896  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 558 896.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Office  August 1989 v110 n2 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Your cable company as your telephone company? (TelecommunicationsInsights)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hargadon, Tom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Because of improvements in the equipment, cable televisioncompanies may soon enter the telephone communications business.andO;Fiber optics, the technology behind improved broadbandtelecommunications, is the same technology responsible for thecable TV industry.andP;  Improvements in equipment and billingpioneered by local and long-distance telephone companies can beused by the upstart cable companies.andP;  Telecommunications hasitself changed and companies today are driven by their MISdepartments.andP;  Management decisions are made based on what servicesare available at the best rate.andP;  Experienced management, while notobsolete, is much less important.andP;  As telephone companies cater tosmall customers with enhanced services such as universal voiceaccess and data access through ISDN, cable companies can carve aniche by servicing the large and moderate customer with broadbandcommunication at lower prices.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TelecommunicationsCable TVISDNBroadbandFiber OpticsTelephone Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>